          ],
          "buttonTool": null,
          "description": null,
          "carouselTool": null,
          "instructions": "Prompt the user to provide their business email address and make sure you are a strict Email Validator. Your job is to validate {email}  from one of three categories: \"valid_business\", \"valid_personal\", or \"invalid_format\".\r\n\r\nRules:\r\n1. INVALID FORMAT: If the input is not a standard email address (e.g. missing \"@\", missing \".com/.net/etc\"), output: Ask the user to provide valid business email address as the format was invalid.\r\n2. PERSONAL EMAIL: If the domain is gmail.com, yahoo.com, hotmail.com, outlook.com, icloud.com, aol.com, protonmail.com, or live.com,  Ask the user to provide valid business email address personal email address are not allowed.\r\n3. BUSINESS EMAIL: If it is a valid email format AND the domain is NOT in the personal list above, store it in the {email} variable.\r\n\r\n",
          "functionTools": [],
          "webSearchTool": null,
          "callForwardTool": null,
